/**
\mainpage env : MCS Environments

\bdesc
This module is a collection of C++ library and comman line utilies to deal with 
MCS environments; e.g. the C++ library allows you to find the host name and port 
number associated with a given environment, and the command line utilites allow 
you to show, start, check end stop MCS environments.

\usedfiles
In MCS all the environments are listed in the mcsEnvList file.
\filename mcsEnvList :  MCS environment definition file, located in $MCSROOT/etc
directory

\n
\env
In MCS, the environment to be used is defined by the value of the $MCSENV
environment variable.
\envvar MCSENV :  MCS environment name to be used

*/
